wikipedia_page.main: Anthony Watson (died 10 September 1605) was an English bishop.

response: Henry Robinson, Anthony Watson, Tobias Matthew, Thomas Dove, Anthony Rudd, Thomas Bilson, Gervase Babington, Deans Lancelot Andrewes, John Overall, James Montague, William Barlow, Giles Tomson and Thomas Ravis. Also John Rainolds (sometimes Reynolds), the president of Corpus Christi College, Oxford. There were three meetings over a period of five days.
